article_title: Hong Kong Protest Site in Mong Kok Cleared by Police, Leaders Arrested
article_text:
HONG KONG—Police cleared the most volatile protest site in Hong Kong and arrested several student protest leaders in an aggressive 24-hour operation that marked a new phase in the two-month-long occupation.

Police were quicker to use batons and to arrest protesters than they had been in the past as they opened roads on Wednesday in the densely populated neighborhood of Mong Kok. Two high-profile student leaders were among the nearly...
